k medical attention if they experience potential signs and symptoms of hepatotoxicity such as fever, rash, itching, anorexia, nausea, vomiting, fatigue, malaise, right upper quadrant pain, dark urine, pale stools, and jaundice.', 'Synergism', 'Caution is advised if mipomersen is used with other potentially hepatotoxic agents (e.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/4513/', '', 'Salicylic acid, Choline salicylate, Ziconotide, Diflunisal, Methoxyflurane, Salsalate, Acetylsalicylic acid, Oxymorphone, Oxycodone, Methadone, Pentazocine, More', 'Fenofibric acid, Pitavastatin, Evinacumab, Evolocumab, Probucol, Dextrothyroxine, Clofibrate, Colestipol, Bempedoic acid, Colesevelam, Alirocumab', 1767369485);
